title: 2010.08.29-F1.13.Belgium.Race.BBC1_UK [TDMK1]
description:
2010.08.29-F1.13.Belgium.Race.BBC1_UK-TDMK1.m4v

Jake Humphrey introduces coverage of the 13th round of the season from Spa-Francorchamps (Start-time 1.00pm). Just 20 points separate the top five drivers in the standings, but Red Bull's Mark Webber is the man in form with victories at Silverstone and the Hungaroring moving the Australian four points clear of Britain and McLaren's Lewis Hamilton. Ferrari have shown signs of improvement in recent races and their record on this track is impressive, having won here for the last three years. Mark Webber starts on pole position. With analysis by Eddie Jordan and David Coulthard, and commentary by Jonathan Legard and Martin Brundle.

Now encoded as 'MP4 All Play'... As a departure from the DivX files which I have uploaded in the past, I've made the decision to get with the 21st century & start encoding with the following specs this year;

MP4 - 640x352 - 800Kb/s H264 Video - 44.1KHz/128Kbps Stereo AAC Audio

My belief is this is the best all round setup, and hopefully you will agree!

This video will play on a computer with VLC, XBMC, XBox360, PS3, iPad all iPhones - enjoy the show... :)
